\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line PC Training is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line The Diploma in Entrepreneurship programme was tabled at the Accreditation Committee Meeting of 27 July 2011 and was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A\line - The programme lacks coherence and the outcomes and the syllabus for most modules do not match. It is therefore unclear what is being taught and thus while the module names seem to suggest a coherent structure there is no evidence of this in the document that outlines the modules.\line - The staff complement at each site is not sufficient in size and experience to teach on the programme.\line - The workload arrangements with regard to the Programme Coordinators and \'E2\'80\'98junior\'E2\'80\'99 staff do not appear to be suitable to ensure quality offering\line - The programme is also NOT accredited to be offered through the distance education mode of delivery\line \line The institution submitted a representation.\line \line \cell \pard 

