\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator of the representation considered the initial evaluators\'27 reports and the additional information submitted by the institution. The evaluator stated that although the Institution claims that the curriculum for the Diploma in Entrepreneurship \'E2\'80\'9Chas been reviewed in its entirety to address the incoherence of the outcomes and syllabus for specific modules\'E2\'80\'9D\'2C it still contains major shortcomings.  Based on the numerous shortcomings identified\'2C the conclusion reached by the evaluator is that the proposed programme has been put together \'28\'E2\'80\'9Ccut and paste\'E2\'80\'9D\'29 by persons who are not competent\'2C either in terms of having not qualified in the subjects whose exit level outcomes and syllabi they were required to draw up\'2C and\'2For having not taught these subjects before.  To ensure the integrity of a programme\'2C it is essential that qualified and experienced persons are involved in drawing up the syllabi and exit level outcomes of the various modules.  Furthermore\'2C those appointed as Programme Managers should be competent to evaluate all of the modules in the proposed programme to check for intellectual depth\'2C for alignment of the exit level outcomes and the syllabus with the number of \'28NQF\'29 credits allocated to a module\'2C as well as with the NQF level of the module \'28i.e. 5\'2C 6 or 7\'29.  In terms of the programme design the evaluator indicated that\'3A\line 1. The exit level outcomes are not commensurate with that which is expected at NQF level 6. \line 2. The syllabi for some of the modules lack sufficient disciplinary content and intellectual depth.  \line 3. There are instances where the learning outcomes of a module are not aligned to the syllabus\'2C as well as an \line overlap of learning outcomes between modules\'2C and of inappropriate learning outcomes.  \line 4. The exit level outcomes and syllabus for Economics 101 and Economics 102 are identical. \line \line The Directorate concurs that the decision not to accredit the programme be upheld. \line \line \cell \pard 

